Now, that's important, because Kiss was specifically talking about how people's perceptions of the high end guilds was affected by threads like this. Which only goes to prove, that perception is everything. People might never even bother to take the time to get to know him on any level because they feel they already do know him from what they have read here on the boards.<br>
<br>
To be honest, I have no problems with TK as a guild. I have alot of friends in TK, people I've known since I was running around the commons and Fay beating the hell out of orcs. I'm simply stating that some people might start to think they are full of snotty people because the only time they get involved in a flame post is to say &quot;we'd never do anything like that, because we're good, resposible people&quot;. Best bet? say &quot;yeah, that's stupid, I hate people who do thoughtless things like that&quot; and let it go at that. If you don't show up on the flame boards as a guild for doing negative things, trust me, people will realize you are nice people all on their own. <p><table border=1>
