<br>
On one hand, as a SK, I try to invis anywhere I go. It's kind of a habit to have my &quot;travel spells&quot; up, which include: ultravision, see invis, invis, darkness and fear. the darkness is good in case i get agroed by something i cant run from... just snare and run. fear is good to just get something  off me to run. FD works too, but it never clears agro, so to hell with that.<br>
<br>
ive run across many a zone and rarely train to the zone. but if i think i might, i tend to FD at the zone, wait a minute, then zone. usually there is no train that way.<br>
<br>
On the OTHER hand, I learned from day 1 (back in blackburrow) that camping near a zone is a bad idea. People are constantly going to be coming and going, training all the way. Unless your group is prepared to handle 50 mobs, dont fight near the zone. It's just unwise. Learn from the mistakes of the newbies, and play smarter <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>~Nnod Fleshripper~<br>
